This is how I feel too.  I never used any protection because I didn&#39;t want
to dilute any experience I have.  Going &quot;comando&quot; as I like to call it. 
However, I posted about a nasty entity that came home with us.  I actually
didn&#39;t think that this would ever happen.  I thought that since I didn&#39;t
think it could happen...that it wouldn&#39;t.  I was wrong.  I still haven&#39;t
used any protection...however, I may use a &quot;you stay here&quot; ritual.

Carol B.



&gt; I may draw some flack from this post but I feel this is a very important
&gt; subject. What exactly are you doing when you use a ritual or prayer for
&gt; protection? You are placing limitations on the session. What is the point
&gt; of doing research in ITC if you are not willing to deal with all aspects
&gt; of it? The enemy is not some nasty entity out there that wants to cuss and
&gt; threaten you, it is your fear. All of us who have been doing this for any
&gt; length of time come across, as Sumption calls them &quot;paper tigers&quot;. They
&gt; bark, bark, bark but have no real bite! Unchecked fear causes the most
&gt; damage both psychologically and physically. This fear (the lack of control
&gt; of it) is also the reason why people make up these rituals.
&gt;
&gt; Regards,
&gt;
&gt; Frank R.
